President Donald J. Trump has proclaimed September 2019 as National Alcohol and Drug Addiction Recovery Month in the United States. The proclamation aims to raise awareness of substance use disorder and celebrate the millions of Americans who have successfully overcome addiction. President Trump highlights the importance of combating the addiction crisis and outlines the actions his administration has taken to address the issue. These actions include the Initiative to Stop Opioid Abuse and Reduce Drug Supply and Demand, the SUPPORT for Patients and Communities Act, and securing funding to help Americans affected by addiction. The proclamation emphasizes the role of individuals and organizations in supporting recovery efforts and encourages all Americans to work towards ending the crisis of alcohol and drug addiction.